editionStmt.p: The images of the manuscript taken by Antonella Brita, Karsten Helmholz and Susanne Hummel during a mission funded by the Sonderforschungsbereich 950 Manuskriptkulturen in Asien, Afrika und Europa, the ERC Advanced Grant TraCES, From Translation to Creation: Changes in Ethiopic Style and Lexicon from Late Antiquity to the Middle Ages (Grant Agreement no. 338756) and Beta maṣāḥǝft.

The images are published in conjunction with this descriptive data about the manuscript with the permission of the Biblioteca Medicea Laurenziana, prot. 190/28.13.10.01/2.23 of the 24 January 2019 and are available for research purposes.

msItem.title: Prayer against Bāryā
msItem.note: Prayer against the evil eye of Bāryā, to bind the demons and to swallow them; with invocation of magical names.
msItem.incipit: በስመአብ፡ ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ዓይነ፡ ባርያ፡ ወማእሰሮሙ፡ ለአጋንንት፡ ወመሰጥመ፡ አጋንንት፡ ጸሎተ፡ አልሚ፡ ያሸሸነጅ፡
msItem.explicit: ሻር፡ ጻዑ፤ ኵልክሙ፡ ፀዋጋን፡ ከመ፤ ኢይቅረቡ፤ ኢ፡ እምላዕለ፡ ገብርከ፡ ገብረ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡

msItem.title: Prayer against demons
msItem.note: Prayer to bind demons, which repeats the headings of the Prayer of Alexander the Great and of the Network of Solomon.
msItem.incipit: በስመአብ፡ ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ማአሰሮሙ፡ ለአጋንንት፡ ዘተናገሮ፡ እስክንድር፡ ንጉሥ፡ በቅድሜሆሙ፡ ለውሉደ፡ ቃየል፡ አስማተ፡ ሰሎሞን፡ ዘረበቦሙ፡ ለአጋንንት፡ ከመ፡ መርበብት፡ አዓሣ፡ ዘባሕር፡ እንዘ፡ ይብል፡ ስድራኤል፡ እልመሬብ፡
msItem.explicit: አልፋ፡ አልፉ፡ ጸልለኒ፡ ኦምጸድፍ፡ አድኅነኒ፡ እምኵሉ፡ ጸላዒ፡ ነደፈ፡ ዓይነት፡ ውፃዕ፡ እምላዕለ፡ ኦገብርከ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡

msItem.title: Prayer against the ʿAyna Warq, Zār and Tǝgridā
msItem.note: Prayer against ʿAyna Warq, Zār, Tǝgridā and other demons, invoking magical names and those of the nails of the Holy Cross.
msItem.incipit: ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ አይነ፡ ወርቅ፡ ፈሪ፡ ሕኩኪ፡ አንቲ፡ ሕማመ፡ ዛር፡ ወትግሪዳ፡
msItem.explicit: ወዘእንበለ፡ ጽዋዕ፡ ዘትሰቲ፡ ደመ፡ ሰብእ፡ ፃዕ፡ አንተ፡ ዓይነ፡ ኩሪ፡ ወባርያ፡ ወለሌዎን፡ ፃዕ፡ ሕቅለ፡ ወተግስ፡ እምላእለ፡ ገብርከ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያ አጅም፡ አጅምጅም፡ ሰፍልል፡ ጸፍ፡ ልል፡ መድቆልል፡ በኃይለ፡ ዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ፡ ፀቶራፍ፡ ቶራኒ፡ ማስደምታ፡ ቶሳ፡ አማኑኤል፡ ሚጥ፡ ልቡ፡ ውስተ፡ ፍኖትከ፡ አድኅኖ፡ እምዝንቱ፡ ዓይነት፡ ለገብርከ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም።

msItem.title: Prayer against Bāryā
msItem.note: Prayer against the evil eye of Bāryā and to bind demons, with a quote from
msItem.incipit: በስመአብ፡ ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ዓይነ፡ ባርያ፡ ወማእሰሮሙ፡ ለአጋንንት፡ ወንጌል፡ ዘዮሐንስ፡ ቀዳሚሁ፡ ቃል፡ ወውእቱ፡ ቃል፡
msItem.explicit: ኢይዘረክቦ፡ ወኢይቀርቦ፡ ከማሁ፡ ኢይቅርብዎ፡ መናፍስት፡ ርኩሳን፡ ወአጋንንት፡ ፀዋጋን፡ ወሰብእ፡ መሰርያን፡ አድኅኖ፡ ለገብርከ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡

msItem.title: Prayer against Šatolāy and Šatolāwit
msItem.note: Prayer against Šatolāy and Šatolāwit, which alludes to Network of Solomon, with invocation of magical names.

incipit.hi: በከመ፡ ረበቦሙ፡ ሰሎሞን፡ ሎፍሐም፡ ሎፍሐም፡ ሎፍሐም፡

msItem.explicit: በማቃለ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ፩አምላክ፡ አንትሙ፡ ሸቶላይ፡ ወሸቶላዊት፡ ተቀጥቀቱ፡ ከመ፡ ገልዕ፡ ይልሳህ፡ ሕምዝከሙ፡ አጋንንት፡ ከመ፡ ኢይቅርቡ፡ ኀበ፡ ነፍሱ፡ ወሥጋሁ፡ ለገብርከ። ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡ ወለተ፡ ኪዳን፡

msItem.title: Prayer against the evil eye
msItem.note: Prayer against the evil eye with mention of Joseph and his bad position similar to .
msItem.incipit: በስመአብ፡ ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ዓይነት። በቀይሕ፡ ወበፀሊም፡ በከመ፡ ወፅአ፡ ዮሴፍ፡ እምሕሱም፡ ፈንታ፡ ፈጸንታ፡ ይቤላሹን፡ አብሹን፡

explicit.hi: ዓይነት፡ ውፃዕ፡ ኩሪ፡ ጹሪ፡ ስቢባመ፡ በልሲብ፡ ድኂብ፡ ድኂብ፡ ረቢ፡ ረቢ፡

msItem.title: Prayer against pleuralgia
msItem.note: Prayer against pleuralgia, with invocation of magical names.
msItem.incipit: በስመአብ፡ ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ውግአት፡ ምድምያኖስ፡ ምድምያኖስ፡
msItem.explicit: ከመ፡ አድኅንኮ፡ ለወልደ፡ ክርሥቂ፡ ከማሁ፡ አድኅኖ፡ እምኅማመ፡ ውግአት፡ ለገብርከ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡

msItem.title: Prayer against the evil eye
msItem.note: Prayer against the evil eye, constituted essentially an invocation to the Lord.
msItem.incipit: በስመአብ፡ አንተ፡ በሰማይ፡ ወአንተ፡ በምድር፡ አንተ፡ ተሐዩ፡ ወአንተ፡ ትቀትል፡ ሕራስ፡ ወንዋም፡ ዘይመጽአከ፡
msItem.explicit: ወአንተ፡ ዘፈቀድከ፡ ትገብር። ውፃዕ፡ ዓይነት፡ አንተ፡ ዓይነት፡ አድኅኖ፡ እምላእለ፡ ነፍሱ፡ ወሥጋሁ፡ ለገብርከ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡

msItem.title: Prayer against diseases
msItem.note: Prayer against diseases, called ፍጌን፡ and አልጕም፡ as well as against the evil eye of Christians, pagans, Jews, Egyptians, Bāryā, Lagǝwon, Zār and others, with invocation of magical names.
msItem.incipit: በስመ፡ ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ፍጌን፡ ወኅማመ፡ አልጕም፡ ወዓይነት፡ ውጭባጅር፡ ውጭባጅር፡ ውጭባጅር፡
msItem.explicit: ወኅማመ፡ ዛር፡ ወሟቋ፡ ወተላዋሽ፡ ወኅማመ፡ ቈረኛ፡ እምሕማመ፡ ፌራ፡ ወንዳድ፡ ወተጻይዠ፡ ለገብርከ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡ እስመአልቦ፡ ነገር፡ ዘይስአኖ፡ ለኢግዚአብሔር፡

handNote.seg: incipits, sacred names, name of owner

decoNote.desc: Large, multi-colored miniature at the top of the scroll depicting two angels, one of them brandishing a sword.

Large, multi-colored miniature in the centre of the scroll on the second strip. of a cross and four angels within a diamond-shaped square and surrounded by four angels with a frame in the form of a multi-colored garland.
Various symbols and ornaments in yellow, red and black in the centre of the scroll on the third strip.
Large, multi-colored miniature, depicting a human face, enclosed by a square, in the center of a cross with arms with triangular edges.

decoDesc.decoNote: Large, multi-colored miniature on the bottom of the scroll depicting two winged figures and containing the words ቃለ፡ ዘእግዚአብሔር፡ ይመትር፡ ነደ፡ ዕሳት።

decoNote.desc: Black line frame the written text with a yellow painted margin.

item.desc: Small round stamp on the top and on the bottom: BIBL. MED. LAUR. FLOR.
"131324" written at the top left in pencil by a recent European hand.
"Acq. e doni 821" written at the top right in pencil by a recent European hand.

decoNote.desc: About 600mm long leather strap to hang the scroll, passing it through a hole in the centre near the top.

projectDesc.p: Encoded according to TEI P5 Guidelines.
